%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHansal%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EFaraaz%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20gritty%20recreation%20of%20the%20terrorist%20attack%20by%20a%20group%20of%20five%20young%20Islamist%20terrorists%20on%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20in%20Dacca%20in%202016.%20The%20assault%20left%20dead%2029%20people%2C%20including%2020%20guests%20in%20the%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20caf%C3%A9%20staff%20and%20policepersons.%20The%20film%20tells%20the%20moving%20story%20of%2020-year-old%20Faraaz%20Ayaaz%20Hossein%2C%20the%20grandson%20of%20a%20leading%20business%20tycoon.%20The%20terrorists%20offer%20to%20let%20him%20walk%20out%20free%20because%20of%20his%20Muslim%20identity%2C%20but%20Faraaz%20refused%20to%20abandon%20his%20two%20friends%20to%20die%20in%20their%20hands%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%20he%20also%20dies%20with%20them.%20Both%20films%20together%20depict%20the%20horrific%20visage%20of%20religious%20hatred%2C%20Hindu%20on%20one%20side%20of%20the%20border%20and%20Muslim%20on%20the%20other%2C%20but%20identical%20in%20many%20ways%20in%20their%20cruelty%20and%20mindless%20violence.%20But%20what%20both%20films%20also%20share%20in%20common%20is%20that%20when%20their%20central%20protagonists%20are%20endangered%20by%20the%20violence%20of%20hate%2C%20they%20choose%20even%20at%20the%20risk%20to%20their%20lives%20to%20hold%20fast%20to%20their%20values%20of%20humanism%2C%20friendship%20and%20decency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20every%20one%20of%20the%20films%20and%20shows%20in%20my%20selection%20this%20year%2C%20when%20light%20fades%20%E2%80%93%20sometimes%20through%20caste%20and%20gender%20oppression%2C%20sometimes%20through%20religious%20hatred%2C%20sometimes%20through%20class%20inequality%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20each%20time%20this%20moral%20arc%20of%20humanism%20that%20pierces%20through%20the%20blackness.%20In%20this%20year%20of%20enveloping%20darkness%2C%20I%20am%20grateful%20that%20the%20best%20of%20popular%20art%20celebrates%20idealism%2C%20courage%20and%20love%20so%20that%20we%20still%20can%20hope.%3C%2Fp%